The paper deals with packet scheduling in a network switch, which is a topic related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The problem of scheduling packets with deadlines involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of online algorithms, which falls under cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of a performance metric, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
